main event: Analysis of an unidentified object observed near Phoenix, Arizona between August 1958 and July 1959.
interesting points: The report involves a bright, luminous object that appeared rectangular and larger than the surrounding landscape., The phenomenon was documented with color slides and a photo analysis report., One photo measuring 4"x6" was mentioned but not included in the document., The report indicates some issues with photo processing that may have affected slide clarity., The analysis was approved by officials from the USAF's Photo Analysis Division.
